The paper discusses multi-task feature learning, which is a common topic in machine learning and computer vision. The use of non-convex learning models and regularization techniques suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes an adaptive threshold component, which is related to feature selection and could be relevant to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-categories. Finally, the empirical studies on both synthetic and real-world data sets suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.SD (Sound) sub-category, which deals with signal processing and data analysis.
